$ GTK+

{ Themes

  The chosen theme controls controls how a GTK+ application looks.

  Apparently, the themes can be configured in → Linux/fhs/home/username/_config/gtk-3_0/settings_ini.

}

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/home/username/_config/gtk-3_0
  → Linux/fhs/home/username/_config/gtk-3_0/bookmarks
  → Linux/fhs/home/username/_config/gtk-3_0/settings_ini

  → Linux/fhs/etc/gtk-2_0/gtkrc

  → Linux/fhs/home/username/_config/gtk-3_0/bookmarks stores bookmarks (for example used in Nautilus)
